%N A395693 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = number of labeled 4-multigraphs on n vertices with clique number exactly k.
%C A395693 A 4-multigraph allows edge multiplicities 0..4. Clique number is defined on the underlying simple graph (multiplicity >=1).
%C A395693 Part of the family T_p(n,k) = Sum_{G: omega(G)=k} p^{e(G)}. Row sums give 5^(n*(n-1)/2).
%C A395693 The range p=1..5 covers typical transportation network interlining depths (metro/tram systems). See cross-references for other p values.
%C A395693 Values computed by weighting simple graph enumeration with 4^{e(G)}; verified for n<=6.
%H A395693 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="/A395693/b395693.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..66</a> (terms 1..36 from Alejandro Zarzuelo Urdiales)
%H A395693 Alejandro Zarzuelo Urdiales, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20004703">Clique-Size Dominance Threshold Distribution Enumerating Labeled Graphs by Clique Number and the Minimum Coding Clique Size</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%H A395693 Alejandro Zarzuelo Urdiales, <a href="https://github.com/alejandrozu/Clique-OEIS">Python verification code and Lean 4 formalization</a>, GitHub.
%F A395693 T(n,k) = Sum_{G: omega(G)=k} 4^{e(G)}.
%F A395693 Row sums: Sum_{k=1..n} T(n,k) = 5^(n*(n-1)/2) = A109345(n).
